text: Accomack County, which used to be called Accomac Shire, is a U.S. county in the Commonwealth of Virginia. The 2020 census said that 33,413 lived there. Its county seat is Accomac. Accomack and Northampton Counties comprise the Eastern Shore of Virginia, part of the Delmarva Peninsula. == References == == Other websites == * Official Website of Accomack County, VA * Accomack County, Virginia Genealogy, History and Records Category:Virginia counties Category:1671 establishments Category:1670s establishments in the Thirteen Colonies Category:17th-century establishments in Virginia
